slides.content:
## Write Comments That Matter

Not all comments are created equal! Follow these professional guidelines:

**✅ Good comments explain *why*:**
```javascript
// Using timeout to wait for animation to finish
setTimeout(doSomething, 300);
```

**❌ Bad comments restate *what* the code does:**
```javascript
// Set x to 5
let x = 5;
```

**Golden Rule**: If your code is clear enough, it shouldn't *need* a comment. Write self-explanatory code first, then add comments only for the *why*.
